Recent reports from PWInsider shed light on WWE superstar Rhea Ripley's unexpected injury, which occurred during a brawl with Liv Morgan. Ripley's injury was a result of being sent into a wall, causing damage to her AC joint, where the collarbone and shoulder connect. The severity of her injury and subsequent recovery time hinge on whether she will require surgery.

Contrary to speculation, the injury was not caused by the chair shot delivered by Liv Morgan during the altercation. This clarification comes from Fightful, which also reports that there is no internal backlash against Morgan for the unfortunate incident. Despite the unintended consequence, there is no apparent heat on Morgan within the WWE organization.

Ripley's injury serves as a reminder of the physical toll that professional wrestling can take on its athletes, with even routine maneuvers carrying the risk of significant harm. As fans await further updates on Ripley's condition and recovery process, the incident highlights the importance of safety protocols and careful execution within the high-octane world of sports entertainment.